T1	Participants 287 412	One group received computer-generated, customized letters explaining recommended preventive procedures for each family member
T2	Participants 414 532	A second group received a form letter listing recommendations for all preventive procedures for all age and sex groups
T3	Participants 534 583	A third group (control group) received no letters
T4	Participants 585 666	SETTING A private medical centre, without university affiliation, in rural Quebec
T5	Participants 668 759	PARTICIPANTS From 8770 patients who met study criteria, 719 families were randomly selected
T6	Participants 761 824	Data were available for 1971 of 1998 patients in these families
T7	Participants 1136 1291	The Family Received Index for families mailed customized letters was more than double the index for patients not mailed letters (Kruskal-Wallis P = .0139).
T8	Participants 1292 1509	Comparison of the Family End-of-study Up-to-date indices also demonstrated that families of patients sent customized letters were more likely to be up-to-date than families not sent letters (Kruskal-Wallis P = .0054).
